Mils Muliaina was arrested last night in connection with an allegation of sexual assault in Cardiff in March . 
  The former All Black was arrested after Connacht lost 14-7 to Gloucester in the European Challenge Cup . 
  The 34-year-old full back denies the allegations and has been bailed . 
  He is accused of assaulting a woman in a bar after a game in Cardiff . 
  He has 100 caps for the All Blacks and retired from rugby in 2011 . 
  He was arrested at the Kingsholm Stadium after the game . 
 